nodes.id: No arrogance like that of the recently humbled
chart another path up the mountain
we _know_ markets and incentives can be manipulated
love and accept all past and future selves
After you die on a hill, you’re kinda dead.
Taxes cannot be deemed regressive or progressive until we know how the funds are spent
Subsidies should be the difference between lifetime damages for gas and electric vehicles
Subsidies are expensive motivators because of the inframarginal costs
Electricity generation and pollution control can cross state lines
States are incentivized to focus on internal pollution, by NAAQS air quality standards
Policymakers tend to implement indirect policies
Cheaper fuel implies that people will drive more
Why everything we teach at SPARC is wrong
World Bank Living Standards and Measurement Survey
